Mr. Shina Peller, member, House of Representatives, representing Iseyin/ Itesiwaju/Kajola Federal Constituency, Oyo State has stated that empowerment of the underprivileged is germane to the socio-economic development of the nation. He stated this on Thursday during the launching of the philanthropic initiative of Mr. Bamidele Omosehin, a business magnate, at Iju-Odo, Okitipupa Local Government Area of Ondo State. Peller emphasised that if the underprivileged were empowered academically and financially, they would enhance the nation’s development greatly. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Commenting on the initiative by Mr. Omosehin, the federal lawmaker, who was in attendance to support the founder, stated that philanthropists should look the way of the underprivileged on how to assist them in terms of skill acquisition, supply of equipment or working tools after training. He described Omosehin as a passionate philanthropist who focused on development and assistance for the underprivileged in the society. Christmas: Diri Foresees Better Days Ahead NBA Felicitates With Nigerians On Christmas Peller, who was the chairman of the launching, promised to bring his intellectual empowerment initiative to Ondo State early next year and supported Bamidele Omosehin Foundation with a donation of one million Naira. In his address, Omosehin described the initiative as a non-profit making with the goal to ameliorate poverty and hardship in the lives of the people of Africa in general and Nigerians particularly. He said that the desire of the initiative is to go about enhancing community healthcare through the provision of free medical services, payment of medical bills for those with health and financial challenges and provision of quality education for children beyond the age of 18 years. Bamidele Omosehin, therefore, promised children of school age in Ondo Southern Senatorial District who are intelligent and ready to study but are from lowly and indigent background the needed assistance that would guarantee their future. Among dignitaries present at the event are the Abodi of Ikale Land, HRM Oba George Babatunde Faduyile, the Ahaba of Ajagba , HRM Oba Ademusayo, the Oniju of Iju Odo, HRH Oba Festus Olumoyegun, Lord Bishop Diocese of the Coast, Rt. rev Oluseyi Pirisola, Ven Ogunfeyimi, Hon.Shina Peller (MHR), Mr. White, and a host of others SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION